oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Sullivan, Leroy M., 1921-1943
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Diary authored by Leroy Sullivan, a native of Chattanooga, Tennessee, during his service in the Royal Canadian Air Force during World War II. Beginning on 1941 January 1, Sullivan recounts his training at the British Commonwealth Air Training Polan station in Fingal, Ontario before his deployment with the Royal Air Force in England.
